objectives.name: Primary Objective
objectives.text: To determine if axicabtagene ciloleucel is superior to standard of care (SOC) as measured by event-free survival (EFS), as determined by blinded central review

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - ORR
objectives.text: To evaluate the effect of axicabtagene ciloleucel compared to SOC on objective response rate (ORR), as determined by blinded central review

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - OS
objectives.text: To evaluate the effect of axicabtagene ciloleucel compared to SOC on overall survival (OS)

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - PFS
objectives.text: To evaluate the effect of axicabtagene ciloleucel compared to SOC on progression-free survival (PFS)

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - DOR
objectives.text: To evaluate the effect of axicabtagene ciloleucel compared to SOC on duration of response (DOR) and duration of complete response among responding subjects, as determined by blinded central review

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - Safety
objectives.text: To evaluate the safety of axicabtagene ciloleucel compared to SOC

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - PRO/QoL
objectives.text: To evaluate the effect of axicabtagene ciloleucel on patient reported outcomes (PROs) and quality of life (QoL) compared to SOC

endpoints.name: Primary Endpoint - EFS
endpoints.text: Event-free Survival (EFS): EFS is defined as the time from randomization to the earliest date of disease progression per the Lugano Classification {Cheson 2014}, commencement of new lymphoma therapy, or death from any cause.

endpoints.name: Key Secondary Endpoint - ORR
endpoints.text: Objective response rate

endpoints.name: Key Secondary Endpoint - OS
endpoints.text: Overall survival

endpoints.name: Secondary Endpoint - Investigator EFS
endpoints.text: EFS based on investigator disease assessments

endpoints.name: Secondary Endpoint - Modified EFS
endpoints.text: Modified EFS based on blinded central review and on investigator disease assessments

endpoints.name: Secondary Endpoint - PFS
endpoints.text: Progression-free survival

endpoints.name: Secondary Endpoint - DOR/CR
endpoints.text: Duration of response and complete response

endpoints.name: Secondary Endpoint - Safety
endpoints.text: Incidence of adverse events and clinically significant changes in safety lab values, including antibodies to axicabtagene ciloleucel

endpoints.name: Secondary Endpoint - QoL EORTC
endpoints.text: Changes from screening to post baseline in the global health status QoL scale and the physical functioning domain of the European Organisation for Research and Treatment of Cancer Quality of Life Questionnaire Cancer-30 (EORTC QLQ-C30)

endpoints.name: Secondary Endpoint - QoL EQ-5D-5L
endpoints.text: Changes from screening to post baseline in the Euro-QOL, Five Dimensions, Five Levels (EQ-5D-5L) index and visual analog scale (VAS) scores

estimands.name: Primary Efficacy Estimand - EFS
estimands.populationSummary: Adult subjects with relapsed/refractory diffuse large B-cell lymphoma (r/r DLBCL) after first-line rituximab and anthracycline-based chemotherapy (ITT population) Summary measure: Hazard ratio (stratified log-rank test).

intercurrentEvents.name: Commencement of new lymphoma therapy
intercurrentEvents.text: Subject starts a new lymphoma therapy before a progression event or death

intercurrentEvents.name: Death
intercurrentEvents.text: Death from any cause prior to disease progression

intercurrentEvents.name: Treatment discontinuation
intercurrentEvents.text: Subject discontinues the assigned treatment arm (e.g., fails to receive CAR T infusion or fails to proceed to ASCT)

estimands.treatment: Axicabtagene ciloleucel (single infusion of 2 x 10^6 anti-CD19 CAR T cells/kg) vs Standard of Care (SOC) therapy (platinum-based salvage chemotherapy followed by HDT-ASCT for responders)
estimands.analysisPopulation: Adult subjects with relapsed/refractory diffuse large B-cell lymphoma (r/r DLBCL) after first-line rituximab and anthracycline-based chemotherapy (ITT population)
estimands.variableOfInterest: Event-free survival (EFS), defined as the time from randomization to the earliest date of disease progression (per Lugano 2014), commencement of new lymphoma therapy, or death from any cause

estimands.name: Key Secondary Efficacy Estimand - ORR
estimands.populationSummary: Adult subjects with relapsed/refractory diffuse large B-cell lymphoma (r/r DLBCL) (ITT population) Summary measure: Odds ratio (stratified Cochran-Mantel-Haenszel test).

intercurrentEvents.name: Death prior to response assessment
intercurrentEvents.text: Subject dies before the first scheduled disease assessment

intercurrentEvents.name: Treatment switching
intercurrentEvents.text: Subject in SOC arm receives CAR T-cell therapy off-protocol

estimands.treatment: Axicabtagene ciloleucel vs Standard of Care (SOC)
estimands.analysisPopulation: Adult subjects with relapsed/refractory diffuse large B-cell lymphoma (r/r DLBCL) (ITT population)
estimands.variableOfInterest: Objective response rate (ORR), defined as the proportion of subjects achieving a best response of CR or PR

estimands.name: Key Secondary Efficacy Estimand - OS
estimands.populationSummary: Adult subjects with relapsed/refractory diffuse large B-cell lymphoma (r/r DLBCL) (ITT population) Summary measure: Hazard ratio (stratified log-rank test).

intercurrentEvents.name: Treatment switching/Crossover
intercurrentEvents.text: Subjects in the SOC arm receiving subsequent cellular therapy

estimands.treatment: Axicabtagene ciloleucel vs Standard of Care (SOC)
estimands.analysisPopulation: Adult subjects with relapsed/refractory diffuse large B-cell lymphoma (r/r DLBCL) (ITT population)
estimands.variableOfInterest: Overall survival (OS), defined as the time from randomization to death from any cause
